message.content:
Reinforcement Learning, Memory-based Learning. 

Reinforcement learning is present in the paper as the authors use methods from optimal control to achieve fast real-time learning of the task within 40 to 100 trials. 

Memory-based learning is also present in the paper as the authors use a memory-based local modeling approach (locally weighted regression) to represent a learned model of the task to be performed. They also develop an exploration algorithm that explicitly deals with prediction accuracy requirements during exploration.
